<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,445,671]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Newly recorded in New Brunswick. Found in open deciduous forests, clearings, thickets, orchards, hedges, meadows, and abandoned fields; active on the foliage of plants, bushes, and trees (
<bibRefCitation author="Larochelle" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" refString="Larochelle, A. &amp; Lariviere, M. - C. (2003) A natural history of the ground-beetles (Coleoptera: Carabidae) of America north of Mexico. Pensoft, Sofia, Bulgaria. 583 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Larochelle &amp; Larivi√®re 
<number box="[267,331,565,591]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Commonly found on goldenrod (Lindroth 
<number box="[859,922,565,591]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1969.0">1969</number>
). Some species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1214,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1214,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known parasitoids on chrysomelids and it is suspected that a parasitic mode of life is common to the whole genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Ball" pageId="11" pageNumber="33" refString="Ball, G. E. &amp; Bousquet, Y. (2000) Carabidae Latreille, 1810. In: Arnett, R. H., Jr. and Thomas, M. C. (Eds.). American Beetles. 1. Archeostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga, Polyphaga: Staphyliniformia. CRC Press, Boca Raton, Florida. pp. 32 - 132." type="journal article" year="2000">
Ball &amp; Bousquet 
<number box="[269,333,645,671]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
